Title 
Designing Visual Branding Assets for Multiple Brands Using Canva 


Aim 
To design essential visual branding assets—logo, channel banner, and video 
thumbnail templates—for two different brands using Canva, in order to understand 
brand consistency, visual identity, and adaptability of design principles across 
multiple brands. 
Objectives 
1.
 
To understand the role of visual branding in digital marketing 
2.
 
To apply basic design principles for social media and video platforms 
3.
 
To use Canva’s free tools for creating digital branding assets 
4.
 
To design branding assets for a predefined brand 
5.
 
To design branding assets for a student-selected or self-created brand 
6.
 
To compare and adapt design styles based on brand identity and target 
audience



Theory 
Importance of Visual Branding 
Visual branding is the visual expression of a brand’s identity through elements such 
as logos, colors, typography, and layout. Strong visual branding: 
● 
Builds instant recognition 
● 
Creates trust and credibility 
● 
Differentiates a brand from competitors 
On platforms like YouTube, thumbnails and banners significantly influence user 
engagement and click-through rates.
Using Canva for Multi-Brand Design 
Canva enables designers to quickly adapt design styles for different brands while 
maintaining consistency within each brand. Designing for multiple brands helps 
students understand: 
● 
Brand positioning 
● 
Target audience differences 
● 
Visual tone adaptation 
Design Scope 
Students are required to design branding assets for two brands: 
Brand 1 (Given Example) 
● 
Brand Name: Tasty Bites Kitchen
 
● 
Category: Cooking tutorials
 
● 
Tone: Warm, friendly, appetizing
 
● 
Target Audience: Home cooks and food enthusiasts
 
Brand 2 (Student Choice) 
● 
Any self-created brand or existing concept such as: 
○ 
Fitness channel 
○ 
Travel vlog 
○ 
Tech review channel 
○ 
Personal brand 
● 
Students must define: 
○ 
Brand name 
○ 
Category 
○ 
Target audience 
○ 
Brand tone






Result 
Visual branding assets were successfully designed for two distinct brands using 
Canva’s free features. The designs demonstrate understanding of brand identity, 
visual consistency, and adaptability of design principles across different content 
niches.
